               <p>THOMAS FINNIS. I am apprentice to Mr. James Smith, a <rs id="t18210411-7-viclabel40" type="occupation">grocer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210411-7-victim133 t18210411-7-viclabel40"></join>, who lives in <placeName id="t18210411-7-crimeloc41">Tower-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18210411-7-crimeloc41" type="placeName" value="Tower-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18210411-7-crimeloc41" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210411-7-off38 t18210411-7-crimeloc41"></join>. On the 19th of February, about half-past seven o'clock, I was weighing up sugar at the back of the shop, and heard some person come in, a bag of loaf sugar was near the door, I turned round, and some person run out, I pursued and overtook him about half way across the street, it was the prisoner. I saw him throw the bag down, I picked it up, there was 12 lbs. of sugar in it.</p>
               <p>WALTER STONE. I am a constable. I heard a noise, ran up, and found the prisoner in custody, the bag was delivered to me.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I never had it.</p>
